  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The operating envelope was extended post-validation to include a paediatric low-body-weight subgroup (10–25 kg patients) requiring reduced flow rates of 0.5–1.2 L/min; the existing validation campaign addressed adult flow rates of 2.5–6.0 L/min only. The credibility team judged that the validated adult flow-rate range provides sufficient mechanistic coverage of the extended paediatric regime on the basis that the dimensionless shear-stress scaling arguments remain applicable, without commissioning new experimental test points or linking updated ValidationResult records for the expanded envelope.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
