      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver version controlled and documented; regression test suite passing.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2021R2 used under institutional software QA plan. Version hash recorded in simulation manifest. Regression suite (150 canonical cases) passed. Achieves Gradation 1 as required for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Observed order of accuracy within 10% of theoretical order for all governing equations.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions confirmed second-order spatial accuracy for momentum and scalar hemolysis transport equations. Observed order 1.93 vs theoretical 2.0. Requirement met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI for primary QoI (NIH) below 5% on production mesh.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation across three mesh levels yielded GCI of 3.1% for NIH on the 8.7 M cell production mesh. Temporal discretisation error assessed via time-step halving; change in NIH < 1.5%. Both criteria satisfied. Note: discretisation study was conducted at adult flow rates; extrapolation to paediatric low-flow regime assumed valid by the assessment team without additional mesh studies at 0.5–1.2 L/min."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) match simulation inputs within stated uncertainty bands.",
      "rationale": "Adult bench test conditions (2.5–6.0 L/min, 2400–3600 RPM, porcine blood haematocrit 35±2%) reproduced in CFD boundary conditions. Fluid temperature held at 37°C ±0.5°C; viscosity characterised by Carreau-Yasuda fit. All five adult operating points reproduced within ±2% of target flow rate. Paediatric operating points were not included in the experimental campaign; the team notes that the same boundary-condition matching methodology would apply but provides no supporting data."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD-predicted NIH within 15% of experimental NIH across all validated operating points.",
      "rationale": "Across five adult operating points, CFD NIH predictions ranged from 4% to 12% relative error versus bench measurements, with RMS error of 8.3%. All points satisfy the 15% acceptance band. The assessment team asserts that equivalent accuracy is expected at paediatric flow rates based on the same power-law hemolysis model, but no experimental comparisons at 0.5–1.2 L/min are available or cited."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (NIH and RH index) directly maps to clinical hemolysis endpoint and regulatory acceptance criterion.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the established in-vitro hemolysis metric per ASTM F1841. The relative hemolysis index RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate provides a direct comparison basis accepted by FDA guidance. QoI relevance is unchanged by the paediatric envelope extension, as the same hemolysis metric applies across patient populations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments span the operating envelope defined in the COU, or a documented extrapolation argument covers any gap.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted in 2021 covered adult CPB flow rates of 2.5–6.0 L/min, which constituted the full operating envelope at time of validation. Following the Q1 2024 expansion of the cleared indication to paediatric patients (0.5–1.2 L/min), the team reviewed the 2021 dataset and concluded that the validated Reynolds number range (Re 3,200–7,800) provides mechanistic coverage of the paediatric regime (Re 600–1,800) through dimensional similarity of the power-law hemolysis source term. This extrapolation argument is documented in internal technical memo TM-2024-03 but is not supported by new experimental data points or an updated ValidationResult record. The factor is assessed as meeting Gradation 2 on the basis of the extrapolation rationale alone.",
      "note": "No ValidationResult covering the paediatric flow regime (0.5–1.2 L/min) has been generated. All linked ValidationResult records predate the Q1 2024 envelope expansion."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver residual convergence documented; iterative error bounded.",
      "rationale": "Not assessed at MRL 2 for this factor; residual convergence to 1e-5 reported in simulation log files as standard practice. Scoped acceptable per MRL 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst.",
      "rationale": "Not formally assessed at MRL 2. Simulation setup files version-controlled and reviewed informally by senior analyst. Acceptable at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence and hemolysis constitutive model selection justified for the flow regime.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on literature consensus for rotating internal flows at the relevant Reynolds numbers. Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger correlation) applied with published coefficients. Model form appropriateness documented in design report DR-2021-07. The assessment team notes the Giersiepen-Wurzinger correlation was calibrated on adult shear-exposure data; applicability at the lower shear levels characteristic of paediatric flow rates is asserted without additional sensitivity analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions) characterised with stated uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Pump geometry digitised from CMM measurements (±0.02 mm). Blood viscosity characterised by Carreau-Yasuda model fit to rheometry data (R²=0.997). Inlet velocity profiles derived from Doppler ultrasound measurements. Uncertainty budget documented in UQ report UQ-2021-02. Paediatric-specific haematocrit range (30–40%) noted as within the adult characterisation range; no separate rheometry for paediatric blood samples performed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Blood sample provenance and preparation documented.",
      "rationale": "Not assessed at MRL 2. Porcine blood samples used per ASTM F1841 protocol; haematocrit adjusted to 35%. Sample preparation recorded in laboratory notebook LN-2021-04. Acceptable at MRL 2 without formal assessment."
    },
    {
